Subject: CDS – Action is required to avoid customs delays
Body: View in browser<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-28B0AEF8E57798B77HQVM3EAEF7676E2AFE495/cr.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_2074348_dtlogotrim.jpg] daviesturner.com<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UP-1/c.aspx> 0330 030 1870 <https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UQ-1/c.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/sys/socnet/linkedin-v2.png]<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UR-1/c.aspx> Air<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624US-1/c.aspx> Logistics<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UT-1/c.aspx> Ocean<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UU-1/c.aspx> Road<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UV-1/c.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_251327_4tilteddaviesturnersidebyside72res1920x.jpg]<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UW-1/c.aspx> If you have already registered for CDS click here: [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_2074551_shutterstock_652023034.jpg]<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UX-1/c.aspx> If you import or export, you need to take action now! HMRC is gradually introducing the Customs Declaration Service (CDS), the long-term replacement to the current Customs Handling of Import and Export Freight (CHIEF) system. The below steps need to be taken to ensure your goods can be imported or exported without interruption. Register for a Government Gateway account Most business will already have a Government Gateway account to access their personal or business tax account. You should use this account to access the Customs Declaration Service (CDS). If you do not have one, you register for a Government Gateway account here.<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UY-1/c.aspx> You must have an EORI number Most businesses moving goods in and out of the UK already have one. If you don't have one, you can apply for an EORI number here.<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UZ-1/c.aspx> Register for the Customs Declaration Service (CDS) Use this link to register for the Customs Declaration Service<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V0-1/c.aspx> this can take up to 5 working days. You'll need your Government Gateway user ID and password as well as: - Your GB EORI number - Your Unique Tax Reference (UTR) number - you can find this here is you don’t know it<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V1-1/c.aspx> - Address of your business held on customs records - Your National Insurance number (if you're an individual or sole trader) - The date you started your business Paying VAT and Duty If Davies Turner (or other freight forwarding companies you work with) are paying your VAT & Duty on your behalf and then invoicing this back to you, nothing will change to this method. If you are accounting for VAT using Postponed VAT accounting<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V2-1/c.aspx>, you will need to access your postponed VAT statement<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V3-1/c.aspx> via the Customs Declaration Service. The other options for paying your VAT and Duty are listed below. You can view your balance and payments in the Customs Declaration Service Financial Dashboard, as well as grant and amend standing authorities for your payment accounts. If you have your own Duty deferment account The Customs Declaration Service uses a separate HMRC bank account to CHIEF, so you’ll need to set up a new direct debit<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V4-1/c.aspx> You will also need to re-authorise Davies Turner (or other freight forwarding companies you work with) to use your deferment account. This is done in the Customs Declaration Service Finance Dashboard. You can also choose: * cash account<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V5-1/c.aspx> – these replace the Flexible Accounting System (FAS), and you’ll be set up with one once you’ve registered for the Customs Declaration Service * immediate payment<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V6-1/c.aspx> by Bacs, CHAPS, online or by telephone banking – you can pay by debit, corporate credit card or cheque * individual guarantee<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V7-1/c.aspx> – you can use these to cover customs duties for one-off or high value imports * general guarantee account<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V8-1/c.aspx> – this allows you to provide multiple guarantees from the same account, and continue importing goods into the UK and pay a disputed amount later once agreed [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_2074348_dtlogotrim.jpg] daviesturner.com<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UP-1/c.aspx> 0330 030 1870 <https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624UQ-1/c.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/sys/socnet/linkedin-v2.png]<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-7HQVM3-1624V9-1/c.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_222933_silvertoolkit_33.jpg] [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_222934_silvertoolkit_3311.jpg] [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_222935_silvertoolkit_3312.jpg] The UK's largest independent Freight & Logistics provider. Services by Road, Sea and Air supported by Logistics facilities throughout the UK. Founded in 1870. Copyright 2018 Davies Turner PLC. All rights reserved. If you do not wish to receive any further information by e-mail of selected products and services from us please unsubscribe.<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1C4UO-28B0AEF8E57798B77HQVM3EAEF7676E2AFE495/uns.aspx>

Subject: Eyes on the £££
Body: Hello, Be it at home or work, I’m pretty certain the vast majority of us are keeping a close eye on the pennies at the moment. What if I told you there’s a way to keep your business’s costs low, without affecting your ability to grow? Too good to be true? Stay with me. Moneypenny ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ Hello, Be it at home or work, I’m pretty certain the vast majority of us are keeping a close eye on the pennies at the moment. What if I told you there’s a way to keep your business’s costs low, without affecting your ability to grow? Too good to be true? Stay with me. Moneypenny<https://68388d90fdf74236806ad0df30554607.svc.dynamics.com/t/t/hU4dnLvGx9uDSSZW0i1N8YerpEx5hISPqaYQIn8Ynd0x/CtWmgZra0gsQOVxqH859aenmN1Ox7ZXeLeiBk4VN6Jkx> has been helping businesses just like yours capture calls<https://68388d90fdf74236806ad0df30554607.svc.dynamics.com/t/t/KEwuraLElML87WSpAxR5X6WJqZMGS3qfY7PvZO4OsC4x/CtWmgZra0gsQOVxqH859aenmN1Ox7ZXeLeiBk4VN6Jkx> in the most cost-effective way possible for over 20 years, securing every opportunity going and delighting clients in the process. We do this by giving you one or more of our experienced receptionists, who you know and trust by name, to look after calls exactly as if based in your office. Just another 30 seconds of your time and I’m done, I promise! The beauty of a service like ours, is that you’re only ever paying for quality 24/7 support when you really need it, rather than having a fully resourced reception team permanently available in-house to answer calls. With your availability at our receptionists’ fingertips, along with the capability to transfer calls to your team in Microsoft Teams<https://68388d90fdf74236806ad0df30554607.svc.dynamics.com/t/t/xaJK4iMIaErYTmzf88EsxFxjTyVc1WR8V4iUNMyI9OMx/CtWmgZra0gsQOVxqH859aenmN1Ox7ZXeLeiBk4VN6Jkx> and even book appointments on everyone’s behalf – your callers will assume they’re chatting to a polite and helpful team member based in your office. I’m keen to see lots of businesses try it, which is why we offer a no-obligation trial. We can have you set up within a matter of days and as the UK’s leading provider, we will quickly get to know you and how you like to work, that's where we're unique. If you like it, we charge monthly. Feel free to hit reply if you have any questions, I'd love to hear what you think. Kind regards, Jess Jess Pritchard - Head of Corporate Sector Moneypenny 0333 202 1005<tel:03332021005> [https://res.cloudinary.com/moneypenny/image/upload/f_png/v1/misc/logo.png]<https://68388d90fdf74236806ad0df30554607.svc.dynamics.com/t/t/a043bXe2I7ztKYZ40iJ9LsvAxtYSkfUkbqAPwiv4fTEx/CtWmgZra0gsQOVxqH859aenmN1Ox7ZXeLeiBk4VN6Jkx> [https://res.cloudinary.com/moneypenny/image/upload/v1/email/facebook.png]<https://68388d90fdf74236806ad0df30554607.svc.dynamics.com/t/t/MWAYVgWV3DBK7KKyJTb7BUdBaErxEyMcEQrThzjzVWgx/CtWmgZra0gsQOVxqH859aenmN1Ox7ZXeLeiBk4VN6Jkx> [https://res.cloudinary.com/moneypenny/image/upload/v1/email/twitter.png] <https://68388d90fdf74236806ad0df30554607.svc.dynamics.com/t/t/zobEy5MWz9r5Sw2KTueZrY9R5fve8b8trjzUgJ63bNox/CtWmgZra0gsQOVxqH859aenmN1Ox7ZXeLeiBk4VN6Jkx> [https://res.cloudinary.com/moneypenny/image/upload/v1/email/linkedin.png] <https://68388d90fdf74236806ad0df30554607.svc.dynamics.com/t/t/VRIMPevxTwQcYlnqI2wOPGtJdZCIo0wdxxl3G0uFVdkx/CtWmgZra0gsQOVxqH859aenmN1Ox7ZXeLeiBk4VN6Jkx> [https://res.cloudinary.com/moneypenny/image/upload/v1/email/Insta.png] <https://68388d90fdf74236806ad0df30554607.svc.dynamics.com/t/t/SmmNNEyg4P335n9ZLK9GUiBWCBsFBrkW1gokRdjEwS8x/CtWmgZra0gsQOVxqH859aenmN1Ox7ZXeLeiBk4VN6Jkx> [https://res.cloudinary.com/moneypenny/image/upload/v1/email/templates/trustpilot.png] <https://68388d90fdf74236806ad0df30554607.svc.dynamics.com/t/t/2sir7VG76rNxHgPlfoilH4sTD3KyGSqIzp2tq1UoPd8x/CtWmgZra0gsQOVxqH859aenmN1Ox7ZXeLeiBk4VN6Jkx> [https://res.cloudinary.com/moneypenny/image/upload/v1/email/dr/Cyber_Essentials__PLUS__Badge__High_Res.png] [https://res.cloudinary.com/moneypenny/image/upload/v1/email/templates/BCA2021_company_3star-email.png] This communication and the information it contains are intended solely for the person or organisation to whom it is addressed. Body: Hi James I have spoken to the guys downstairs and 1. We have found a jig. 2. The height of the support bars is 45mm not 450mm 3. The support struts which go under the cabin car will be the same as the front bumpers you fabricate for us, the one where the 2 struts become a solid plate with two holes. 4. The smaller uprights I have been informed are usually made with a small cut and then slight bent into shape. As luck would have it we have a car in for some repairs and they have a bull bar which if it would be helpful we could possibly bring down to you, I will just to check this with production as I am not sure when it is due to go back to the customer. Subject: Would Round House Limited like to take part?
Body: [https://ai-global-image-host.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/guids/CABINET_c8c01103a942854854eef54f8fe048dd/images/view_in_browser_3.png]<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/webviews/4-59528483-1244-13803-13787-25592-pdd99afc66> [https://ai-global-image-host.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/guids/CABINET_c8c01103a942854854eef54f8fe048dd/images/build_2022_construction_and_engineering_awards_nomination_received_jpg.jpg] Awards<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/click/2-59528483-1244-13803-25592-58201-30d2e85e1f-n767af9008> About Us<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/click/2-59528483-1244-13803-25592-58202-07a2abda88-n767af9008> Magazine<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/click/2-59528483-1244-13803-25592-58203-fa8f2b5313-n767af9008> Hi I hope you’re well! Would Round House Limited like the opportunity to win a professional business award? Studies have shown that businesses which regularly enter and win awards report increased sales and income against businesses who don’t enter awards. The research team at BUILD have highlighted you as a potential nominee for the Construction & Engineering Awards 2022. The Construction & Engineering Awards 2022 aim to recognise businesses of all sizes, from SMEs to larger multi-national organisations. Incorporating all variations of enterprises across the construction and engineering disciplines, the Construction & Engineering Awards 2022 welcome nominations from a variety of firms within the industry, regardless of the size or how long the organisation has been established. To confirm your place on the 2022 shortlist, simply click 'Count Me In' below or feel free to respond via email with your confirmation. We do offer a complimentary package as well as a variety of paid additional benefits for our winners, but these are completely optional and merely supplementary to your award rather than essential. Subject: Workshops About Selling Your Business
Body: PREPARING & SELLING YOUR BUSINESS WORKSHOP Workshops are held online via Zoom 10.00 to 12.30 The workshop costs £95.00 BOOKINGS Our website contains booking links allowing you to pay by debit card, credit card or paypal plus feedback comments from past participants. Google sme workshops to visit our website. FORTHCOMING DATES Friday 10 June 2022 Friday 24 June 2022 Friday 08 July 2022 Friday 22 July 2022 Friday 05 August 2022 Friday 26 August 2022 TOPICS COVERED When is the right time to sell? How much is my business worth? What is the likely success rate? How long will it take to sell? How many enquiries will I get? Are there businesses that are certain to sell? Are there businesses that get no interest? What puts buyers off? Who are the buyers? Who are not buyers? Will my close competitors buy? Who are the best buyers? Why do they buy? Should I discount the price? What does a business broker do? Can I sell without a broker? How can I spot the good and the bad business brokers? How should I negotiate? Should I accept staged payments? How can I keep down professional fees? What is the ideal size of business to sell? Is my business too personal to sell? How much work should I as owner be doing? What should sale information look like? Do I need to use confidentiality agreements? What is due diligence? What are heads of agreement? How much will a sale contract cost? What is a non-compete clause? Are my customer records right? Are my marketing systems good enough? How should I arrange my IT systems? Are my accounts right for a sale? What is the difference between a share sale and an asset sale? Am I prepared for an asset sale? Will I be paying too much tax on a sale? PARTICIPANTS The workshops are open to owners of businesses of all sizes and profit levels who are looking to sell their business either now or in a few years time. People who provide advice to businesses are also welcome. TRAINER The workshop will be run by Ian Benson from Matrix Mergers who has sold more than 200 businesses over 20 years as a business broker. SME Workshops 18 Blake Street, York YO1 8QG 01133 280988 To unsubscribe send a blank e-mail to unsubscribe667880@smemail1.co.uk quoting dcc@roundhouselimited.co.uk in the subject line. Unsubscribe requests will take effect within 7 days.

Subject: CDS – Requirements to avoid customs delays
Body: View in browser<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-28B0AEF8E57798B77HQVM3EAEF7676E2AFE495/cr.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_2074348_dtlogotrim.jpg] daviesturner.com<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6A2-1/c.aspx> 0330 030 1870 <https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P69W-1/c.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/sys/socnet/linkedin-v2.png]<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15W9JT-1/c.aspx> Air<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P69S-1/c.aspx> Logistics<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P69T-1/c.aspx> Ocean<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P69U-1/c.aspx> Road<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P69V-1/c.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_251327_4tilteddaviesturnersidebyside72res1920x.jpg]<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P69X-1/c.aspx> If you have already registered for CDS click here: [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_2074551_shutterstock_652023034.jpg]<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15PGFD-1/c.aspx> If you import or export, you need to take action now! HMRC is gradually introducing the Customs Declaration Service (CDS), the long-term replacement to the current Customs Handling of Import and Export Freight (CHIEF) system. The below steps need to be taken to ensure your goods can be imported or exported without interruption. Register for a Government Gateway account Most business will already have a Government Gateway account to access their personal or business tax account. You should use this account to access the Customs Declaration Service (CDS). If you do not have one, you register for a Government Gateway account here.<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6X9-1/c.aspx> You must have an EORI number Most businesses moving goods in and out of the UK already have one. If you don't have one, you can apply for an EORI number here.<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XA-1/c.aspx> Register for the Customs Declaration Service (CDS) Use this link to register for the Customs Declaration Service<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XB-1/c.aspx> this can take up to 5 working days. You'll need your Government Gateway user ID and password as well as: - Your GB EORI number - Your Unique Tax Reference (UTR) number - you can find this here is you don’t know it<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XC-1/c.aspx> - Address of your business held on customs records - Your National Insurance number (if you're an individual or sole trader) - The date you started your business Paying VAT and Duty If Davies Turner (or other freight forwarding companies you work with) are paying your VAT & Duty on your behalf and then invoicing this back to you, nothing will change to this method. If you are accounting for VAT using Postponed VAT accounting<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XD-1/c.aspx>, you will need to access your postponed VAT statement<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XE-1/c.aspx> via the Customs Declaration Service. The other options for paying your VAT and Duty are listed below. You can view your balance and payments in the Customs Declaration Service Financial Dashboard, as well as grant and amend standing authorities for your payment accounts. If you have your own Duty deferment account The Customs Declaration Service uses a separate HMRC bank account to CHIEF, so you’ll need to set up a new direct debit<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XF-1/c.aspx> You will also need to re-authorise Davies Turner (or other freight forwarding companies you work with) to use your deferment account. This is done in the Customs Declaration Service Finance Dashboard. You can also choose: * cash account<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XG-1/c.aspx> – these replace the Flexible Accounting System (FAS), and you’ll be set up with one once you’ve registered for the Customs Declaration Service * immediate payment<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XH-1/c.aspx> by Bacs, CHAPS, online or by telephone banking – you can pay by debit, corporate credit card or cheque * individual guarantee<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XI-1/c.aspx> – you can use these to cover customs duties for one-off or high value imports * general guarantee account<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6XJ-1/c.aspx> – this allows you to provide multiple guarantees from the same account, and continue importing goods into the UK and pay a disputed amount later once agreed [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_2074348_dtlogotrim.jpg] daviesturner.com<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P6A2-1/c.aspx> 0330 030 1870 <https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P69W-1/c.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/sys/socnet/linkedin-v2.png]<https://email.daviesturner.com/4CR4-1BRGY-7HQVM3-15P7Y9-1/c.aspx> [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_222933_silvertoolkit_33.jpg] [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_222934_silvertoolkit_3311.jpg] [https://i.emlfiles4.com/cmpimg/2/5/1/3/0/2/files/imagecache/2228434/w660_222935_silvertoolkit_3312.jpg] The UK's largest independent Freight & Logistics provider. Services by Road, Sea and Air supported by Logistics facilities throughout the UK. Founded in 1870. Copyright 2018 Davies Turner PLC. All rights reserved. The same can also be said for the rest of your team, who may be finding it hard to concentrate at work when they have a health worry that’s keeping them awake at night. That’s why our Health at Hand service is here to support you and your people, whatever your health concern or question is. Whether it’s to do with your own health or your child’s, our expert team of nurses, counsellors, midwives and pharmacists are on hand to help put your mind at ease. Body: [https://ai-global-image-host.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/guids/CABINET_c8c01103a942854854eef54f8fe048dd/images/view_in_browser_3.png]<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/webviews/4-59528483-1244-13797-13781-25509-l2c0c843ba> [https://ai-global-image-host.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/guids/CABINET_c8c01103a942854854eef54f8fe048dd/images/build_2022_construction_and_engineering_awards_nomination_received_jpg.jpg] Awards<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/click/2-59528483-1244-13797-25509-58046-f675601067-gb7136f4f5> About Us<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/click/2-59528483-1244-13797-25509-58047-c2aadb6029-gb7136f4f5> Magazine<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/click/2-59528483-1244-13797-25509-58048-54b0420992-gb7136f4f5> Hi I hope you’re well! Would Round House Limited like the opportunity to win a professional business award? Studies have shown that businesses which regularly enter and win awards report increased sales and income against businesses who don’t enter awards. The research team at BUILD have highlighted you as a potential nominee for the Construction & Engineering Awards 2022. The Construction & Engineering Awards 2022 aim to recognise businesses of all sizes, from SMEs to larger multi-national organisations. Incorporating all variations of enterprises across the construction and engineering disciplines, the Construction & Engineering Awards 2022 welcome nominations from a variety of firms within the industry, regardless of the size or how long the organisation has been established. To confirm your place on the 2022 shortlist, simply click 'Count Me In' below or feel free to respond via email with your confirmation. [https://ai-global-image-host.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/guids/bannerImgGuid/images/image16524372229668370.png]<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/click/2-59528483-1244-13797-25509-58050-69833d3bc0-gb7136f4f5> Count Me In<http://response.build-review.com/Response/Positive/?emailAddress=dcc%40roundhouselimited.co.uk&publication=BUILD&contactIdentifier=ae1c6d78-2f55-414c-942b-6986c8f176a4> If you’d prefer to not progress your nomination, please click “Not This Year”. Not This Year<http://response.build-review.com/Response/Negative/?emailAddress=dcc%40roundhouselimited.co.uk&publication=BUILD&contactIdentifier=ae1c6d78-2f55-414c-942b-6986c8f176a4> Nominees for the Construction & Engineering Awards 2022 are judged based on merit only, not the number of votes received. As such, our internal research team will carefully analyse any information available online and in the public domain, including any material provided by the nominees. Our process is to reward the parties for their industry excellence, overall performance, customer experience and amazing innovation. As with all our awards on BUILD there are no compulsory costs in accepting a nomination or winning an award. We do offer a complimentary package as well as a variety of paid additional benefits for our winners, but these are completely optional and merely supplementary to your award rather than essential. Should you have any questions at all please don’t hesitate to contact me or please visit our FAQ page HERE<http://ga.buildreview-mail.com/ga/click/2-59528483-1244-13797-25509-58049-56f8767169-gb7136f4f5>. ERIKS and Simalube help to give this distiller a reason to celebrate! If you enjoy a whisky now and again, you probably also enjoy a top-up. But when you’re responsible for lubricating your mechanical assets, topping-up is just one more time-consuming, costly, and sometimes potentially dangerous task. So let’s raise a glass to one of Scotland’s leading distilleries, who – with ERIKS’ help – found a way to simplify their lubrication regime. NSK show us life under the hygiene regime Hygiene is the key ingredient in food and beverage manufacturing. Complying with stringent hygiene standards demands frequent thorough washdowns to remove dirt and unwanted grease, often at high pressure with chemical cleaning agents. This can often damage sealing systems – allowing water and cleaning solutions into the bearing cavity, and leading to grease washout, corrosion, and – ultimately – reduced bearing life. Subject: Building a meaningful workplace for your team
Body: Weekly news, tips & laughs :) - [https://braze-images.com/image_uploads/files/6293d7ab93b1c05894c96835/original.png?1653856171] May 31, 2022 The monday.com weekly monday’s take on the latest work trends - sent on Tuesdays Inside this issue * Workplace trends * Building a meaningful workplace for your team * Quotable news * Question of the week * Just for laughs Workplace trends Labor force 40% of recent job switchers are looking for a new position again. According to a recent survey by Grant Thornton, 21% of American workers left their jobs within the last 12 months, and 40% of them are already looking for a new one. LinkedIn data also revealed that the share of job switchers who had been at their previous employer for less than a year increased by 6.5% from 2020 to 2021. While some take these statistics to mean that job switchers must be experiencing buyer’s remorse, others think they’ve just unlocked the secret to increasing their compensation – according to the Federal Reserve Bank of Atlanta, hourly wages for those who changed jobs rose 5.6% in April, compared to 4.2% for those who stayed. And, among the workers who took a new job last year, 40% reported a pay increase of at least 10%, which is more than double the other survey respondents. Labor market CEOs are getting much bigger raises than their workers, according to an article in last week’s AP News. Recent Equilar data revealed that in 2021, CEOs in the S&P 500 saw their annual compensation packages jump 17.1% to a median of $14.5 million, while private sector workers only saw a 4.4% increase. It’s important to note that CEO compensation is often tied to stock and options that cannot be exercised unless the company meets its goals, and that typically only around 25% of their pay package is liquid. Nevertheless, the gap between CEO and rank-and-file worker compensation is getting bigger. At 50% of the organizations surveyed this year, it would take a worker at the middle of the company’s pay scale more than 186 years to earn what their CEO made just last year. Not surprisingly, many are unhappy with these statistics, and workers and investors alike are starting to push back. Diversity & Inclusion Spain is about to become the first Western country to offer menstrual leave that would allow women with a doctor’s note for severe period pain to take government-funded paid time off (PTO). While certain forms of menstrual leave have long existed in a few countries, including Japan, Indonesia, and Zambia, none are as robust as Spain’s. The policy proponents believe this is an important step in destigmatizing menstruation, while critics argue the bill could harm women in the workforce by feeding into sexist stereotypes about periods making women inferior workers. Some experts propose simply offering unlimited sick leave that employees can use however they choose to avoid awkward and invasive conversations. Follow monday insights LinkedIn<https://clicks.mail.monday.com/f/a/QvrQLMuQvt_rp2xkzeqp3g~~/AAQRxQA~/RgRkeOGEP0QwaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGlua2VkaW4uY29tL2NvbXBhbnkvbW9uZGF5LWluc2lnaHRzVwNzcGNCCmKGhFyWYrYYknNSHG1hcmtAcm91bmRob3VzZWxpbWl0ZWQuY28udWtYBAAAALs~> for work-related knowledge, trends, laughs, and insights – we hope this page can serve as a space for deeper understanding, open dialogue, and thoughtful conversation. Building a meaningful workplace for your team by monday.com [https://braze-images.com/image_uploads/files/6293d7ab93b1c05894c96836/original.jpg?1653856171]<https://clicks.mail.monday.com/f/a/oKw4N6VSQTTR-o4GKeDfMg~~/AAQRxQA~/RgRkeOGEP0QwaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj1MbmRkWVdVUGJGSSZ0PTFzVwNzcGNCCmKGhFyWYrYYknNSHG1hcmtAcm91bmRob3VzZWxpbWl0ZWQuY28udWtYBAAAALs~> While many discussions around the Great Resignation have focused on employees’ desire for increased pay, there’s a large body of evidence suggesting that wages only play a small role in employee turnover. In fact, MIT Sloan Review’s recent survey revealed that compensation actually ranked 16th in the list of terms predicting employee turnover. Instead, more and more findings are pointing to culture as the greater predictor of employee attrition. In a recent interview with the New York Times, Benjamin Zweig, a labor economist who teaches at New York University’s Stern School of Business, expanded on this research, explaining that the companies with the highest ratings from their employees in the past year were those that had some connection to the pandemic itself – medical research organizations and even food-delivery services – leading him and other experts to conclude that workers are more satisfied with their jobs, and more likely to stay, when they feel their work matters. So, how do you make work meaningful for your employees? Promote growth and mobility Workers are increasingly eager to see opportunities for learning, development, and advancement in their workplace. In addition, recent research from Cornell University’s School of Industrial and Labor Relations shows that those who have moved internally within a company not only tend to be high performers, but are also more likely to stay with the organization over time. In fact, the highest performing internal hires tend to stay the longest. While it is important to note that while some employees are looking for promotions, research suggests that many are not necessarily interested in additional work and responsibilities. Rather, they are simply seeking new challenges and the chance to explore something different. According to the MIT Sloan Review, lateral career opportunities are 12x more predictive of employee retention than promotions. So, to create a meaningful work experience for your employees, give them opportunities for growth, movement, and the development of new skills. Build relationships When employees feel they belong, they are 3.5x more likely to contribute to their full potential and are significantly more likely to feel connected to their work, according to research from the Harvard Business Review. That’s why company-organized social events, like happy hours, team-building excursions, dinners, and other fun activities outside the workplace are a great way to promote a healthy corporate culture, help your team members connect to each other, and increase their sense of belonging at work. Give your employees a voice Employees tend to feel more connected to their work when they have a real voice on the team – the ability to influence decisions and processes. IBM research found that 90% of workers said that they are likely to stay at a company that takes and acts on their feedback. So, whenever possible, give your employees the chance to contribute their ideas, encourage them to take ownership, and involve them in decision-making processes. Convey impact When employees recognize the impact of their day-to-day activities, they are much more likely to find their work meaningful. So, take the time to help your team members understand how their role connects to your company mission and values. It can be useful to share relevant customer testimonials with your team to highlight the ways in which their efforts are affecting others and helping the company achieve its goals. Quotable News The UK government was partying during lockdown. A new report released last week described how British Prime Minister Boris Johnson and his staff permitted at least 16 boozy government parties at the same time as government-introduced Covid regulations barred any socializing. While Johnson acknowledged his accountability for what’s become known as “partygate”, he insisted that he would not resign. “Above all, I take full responsibility for everything that took place on my watch” Boris Johnson, UK Prime Minister The NBA is taking a stand on gun control. Just before tipoff at last week’s playoff game between the Miami Heat and the Boston Celtics, the Heat’s stadium announcer urged fans to advocate for gun reform laws, following the Texas elementary school shooting. “The Heat urges you to contact your state senators by calling 202-224-3121 to leave a message demanding their support for common sense gun laws” Stadium announcer, Miami Heat Question of the week LAST WEEK’S ANSWER: 94% This week: What’s the #1 city for work-life balance? Subject: Round House Limited "Строительство фонтанов от профессионалов"
Body: From: Antonioefr Subject: Строительство фонтанов от профессионалов Message Body: В проектировании публичных зон больших и маленьких городов наиболее востребованы сухие фонтаны. Это отличный вариант преобразить сквер, территорию рядом с магазином, отелем, деловым центром, кафе и культурным заведением. Эти места становятся запоминающимся местом досуга людей всех возрастных групп. Сухой фонтан отличается тем, что его разрешено устанавливать на любой территории, где есть горизонтальная плоскость. Водная система подобных объектов монтируется ниже уровня земли, за счет чего в другое время территория может использоваться под любые цели. Организация https://fontan-stroy.net.ua рекомендует купить пешеходные фонтаны обычного или интерактивного типа: с подсветкой, музыкальным сопровождением, возможностью управления. В нашей компании оформить заказ на проектирование сухого фонтана для открытых пространств или общественных помещений из долговечных материалов с профессиональным монтажом. Цена сухого фонтана считается индивидуально в зависимости от объема и сложности работ. Все услуги по проектированию и строительству фонтанов - сухой фонтан проектирование и строительство фонтанов сухой фонтан цена строительство больших фонтанов сухой фонтан купить сухой фонтан купить строительство фонтанов под ключ проектирование сухого фонтана заказать строительство фонтана заказать строительство фонтана строительство фонтанов киев сухой фонтан цена пешеходные фонтаны цена стоимость строительства фонтана сухой фонтан пешеходные фонтаны цена строительство фонтана цена сухий фонтан строительство фонтанов киев фонтаны строительство строительство и реконструкция фонтанов проектирование сухого фонтана строительство фонтана цена строительство пешеходного фонтана строительство городских фонтанов стоимость строительства фонтана строительство фонтанов под ключ сухий фонтан сухой фонтан проектирование и строительство фонтанов -- This e-mail was sent from a contact form on Round House Limited (https://roundhousefabrication.co.uk)
